edu.cnm.deepdive.videopoker.model.entity

Class PokerHand

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.cnm.deepdive.videopoker.model.entity.PokerHand

  • public class PokerHand
extends Object
    This is a database entity associated with a winning hand for a game of poker. It contains a name, the ID of the paytable it is associated with, the rule sequence (see Converter class for more details), the value of a one credit bet, and optionally the distinct value of a five (max) credit bet. It also contains a "showInValue" flag to determine if it should appear in displays to the user - this should be false for zero value (bust) hands or for duplicate hands.
